"a position\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"the last tournament\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's why there is a bit of uncertainty about the summer because I am not sure what will happen with that.\\\"\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"uncertainty\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1243}, {\"ngram\": \"the summer\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics would be a fitting farewell for Murray.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 2.960068784631552e-13, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"a fitting farewell\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won singles gold at London 2012 and again at the Rio Games in 2016.\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1389, \"end\": 1400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999985135529775, \"rank\": 1.2692271452787985e-06, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"singles gold\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He would be well down the pecking order for a singles berth currently but could be an option alongside Joe Salisbury, with whom he reached the men's doubles quarter-finals at the last Olympics in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\":